{"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"@","kind":"attribute"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:ScM","kind":"attribute","text":"MainActor"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"OUDSBulletList"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"mentions":["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/ContentDisplay"],"kind":"mentions"},{"content":[{"text":"Types","type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Types"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Three types are proposed:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Unordered (by default)","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":": Collects related items that don’t need to be in a specific order or sequence.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Ordered","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":": Collects related items with numeric order or sequence.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Bare"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":": An unordered list without any bullets or alphanumeric sequence.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Types can be mixed in list, but must be identical for the same ","type":"text"},{"code":"OUDSBulletList.NestedLevel","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},{"text":"Levels","type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Levels"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Lists can include nested items to indicate hierarchy or subcategories, with indentation distinguishing each level.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Arrange ordered list items logically, such as ranking by importance, highest to lowest values, or in alphabetical \/ numeric order.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Three levels are maximum.","type":"text"}]},{"level":2,"text":"Text Style","type":"heading","anchor":"Text-Style"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"List can be used with different font sizes:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Body Large","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":": If the text accompanying the list component is the Body Large text. This variant is designed for more visual, engaging experiences.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Body Medium","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":": If the text accompanying the list component is the Body Medium text. This variant is best suited for functional, task-oriented experiences.","type":"text"}]}]}]},{"level":2,"text":"Cases forbidden by design","type":"heading","anchor":"Cases-forbidden-by-design"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"it is not allowed to have a depth of items greater than 3","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"}]},{"level":2,"text":"Internationalisation considerations","type":"heading","anchor":"Internationalisation-considerations"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"For latin-based speaking countries, like France, Spain, United Kingdom or Belgium, the european “arabic” numbers are used for the first level of depth","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"of the ordered bullet list. For the second and third levels, the european alphabets are used with upper and lower case values.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"However for countries speaking arabic, these rules can’t be applied. Indeed, there is no notion of upper and lower case characters in arabic alphabet.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"In addition, the numbers in use (i.e. the european “arabic” numbers like “1, 2, 3”) are accepted in arabic countries, even if the “true arabic” numbers (like “ ٢ ٣ ١”) are used","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"in middle-east arabic countries and for official documents.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Thus the OUDS ordered bullet list will use “european” numbers for first level, and arabic alphabets for second and third levels.","type":"text"}]},{"level":2,"text":"Code samples","type":"heading","anchor":"Code-samples"},{"code":["       \/\/ 1. Unordered list with bullets","       OUDSBulletList {","           OUDSBulletList.Item(\"Label 1\")","           OUDSBulletList.Item(\"Label 2\")","           OUDSBulletList.Item(\"Label 3\")","       }","","       \/\/ 1.1. Item of Unordered list with bullet as tick, a text style","       \/\/ body medium and text bold","       OUDSBulletList(type: .unordered(asset: .tick),","                      textStyle: .bodyMedium,","                      isBold: true)  {","           OUDSBulletList.Item(\"Label 1\")","           OUDSBulletList.Item(\"Label 2\")","           OUDSBulletList.Item(\"Label 3\")","       }","","       \/\/ 2. Bare list with 3 items","       OUDSBulletList(type: .bare) {","           OUDSBulletList.Item(\"Label 1\")","           OUDSBulletList.Item(\"Label 2\")","           OUDSBulletList.Item(\"Label 3\")","       }","","       \/\/ 3. Ordered list with 3 items","       OUDSBulletList(type: .ordered) {","           OUDSBulletList.Item(\"Label 1\")","           OUDSBulletList.Item(\"Label 2\")","           OUDSBulletList.Item(\"Label 3\")","       }","","       \/\/ 3.1. Ordered list with 3 items in first level,","       \/\/ and one item as sub item (second level),","       \/\/ and 2 items as sub item in (third level)","       OUDSBulletList(type: .ordered) {","           OUDSBulletList.Item(\"Label 1\") {","               OUDSBulletList.Item(\"Label 1.1\") {","                   OUDSBulletList.Item(\"Label 1.1.1\")","                   OUDSBulletList.Item(\"Label 1.1.2\")","               }","           }","           OUDSBulletList.Item(\"Label 2\")","           OUDSBulletList.Item(\"Label 3\")","       }","","       \/\/ Same Bullet list but items in third level with free icon as bullet","       let icon = Image(decorative: \"ic_heart\")","       OUDSBulletList(type: .ordered) {","           OUDSBulletList.Item(\"Label 1\") {","               OUDSBulletList.Item(\"Label 1.1\", subListType: .unordered(asset: .icon(icon))) {","                   OUDSBulletList.Item(\"Label 1.1.1\")","                   OUDSBulletList.Item(\"Label 1.1.2\")","               }","           }","           OUDSBulletList.Item(\"Label 2\")","           OUDSBulletList.Item(\"Label 3\")","       }"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"level":2,"text":"Design documentation","type":"heading","anchor":"Design-documentation"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"https:\/\/r.orange.fr\/r\/S-ouds-doc-bullet-list","isActive":true,"type":"reference"}]},{"level":2,"text":"Themes rendering","type":"heading","anchor":"Themes-rendering"},{"level":3,"text":"Orange","type":"heading","anchor":"Orange"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"component_bullet_list_Orange","type":"image"}]},{"level":3,"text":"Orange Compact","type":"heading","anchor":"Orange-Compact"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"component_bullet_list_OrangeCompact","type":"image"}]},{"level":3,"text":"Sosh","type":"heading","anchor":"Sosh"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"component_bullet_list_Sosh","type":"image"}]},{"level":3,"text":"Wireframe","type":"heading","anchor":"Wireframe"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"component_bullet_list_Wireframe","type":"image"}]},{"name":"Version","style":"note","type":"aside","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"1.0.0 (Figma component design version)","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"name":"Since","style":"note","type":"aside","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"1.2.0","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"ki